but just left out on the floor or in a dirty clothes hamper would not count
because the &quot;master's&quot; intent was not to give them to their elf, but they
still would want the elf to wash them.  IMO elves were doing all the laundry
for their masters, and all the laundry at Hogwarts.

However, I don't think Hermione or any other student counted as a &quot;master.&quot;
BUT the elves still knew Hermione's intent by leaving the clothes scattered
around Gryffindor Tower was to &quot;trick&quot; them into freeing themselves.  THIS
was a grave insult to the elves even if it really wouldn't free them and
that is why only Dobby would clean the tower.  Look at how the elves reacted
to Hermione when she visited the kitchens in GoF and told them they should
be free.

